    Demo Task 07 - Witness interview prep (Open / Investigation)
    ====================================================================

    Synthetic seed record for the case-management POC scoped application.
    This file is the SEVENTH of the 8-task demo dataset; together with
    tasks 01 through 06 and task 08, it satisfies the AAP requirement
    (Section 0.7.4) of providing demo tasks that exercise the resolve-
    blocker and resolve-success gates on both case-type flows. The
    complete 8-task fixture matrix:

        Task 01 - Open        / Investigation / parent case 03 (In Progress GI)
        Task 02 - Closed      / Investigation / parent case 03 (In Progress GI)
        Task 03 - Open        / Follow-up     / parent case 04 (Pending GI)
        Task 04 - Closed      / Investigation / parent case 05 (Resolved GI)
        Task 05 - Closed      / Review        / parent case 05 (Resolved GI)
        Task 06 - In Progress / Investigation / parent case 08 (In Progress Complaint)
        Task 07 - Open        / Investigation / parent case 08 (In Progress Complaint)  ## THIS FILE
        Task 08 - Closed      / Review        / parent case 09 (Resolved Complaint)

    The 8-task dataset thus exercises:
      * All 4 task types - this task contributes one of four Investigation
        entries (the others are tasks 01, 04, and 06); the Investigation
        type semantically represents the agent's evidence-gathering and
        information-collection action on a case.
      * All 3 task statuses (Open, In Progress, Closed) - this task
        contributes the THIRD of the three Open tasks (the others are
        tasks 01 and 03); the Open status is the initial state for a
        newly-created task and is one of the two non-Closed states that
        the validate_resolved_transition subflow treats as a resolve-
        blocker for the parent case.
      * 5 unique parent cases (03, 04, 05, 08, 09) - this task is the
        SECOND child of case 08 (the first being task 06); together,
        tasks 06 + 07 give case 08 TWO non-Closed child tasks
        (In Progress + Open), demonstrating that the resolve gate's
        GlideRecord query correctly counts ALL non-Closed children, not
        just the first one encountered.
      * Both flow paths (General Inquiry and Complaint) - tasks 06 + 07
        together test the COMPLAINT flow's resolve-BLOCKER path; tasks
        01 + 02 test the GENERAL INQUIRY flow's resolve-blocker path;
        tasks 04 + 05 test the GENERAL INQUIRY flow's resolve-success
        path; task 08 tests the COMPLAINT flow's resolve-success path.
      * Both resolve outcomes (BLOCKED via at least one non-Closed task,
        and SUCCESS via zero non-Closed tasks) - this task is the
        SECOND blocker on case 08 (paired with task 06), reinforcing
        that the resolve-blocker fires whenever the count of non-Closed
        children is >= 1, regardless of whether that count is 1 or many.

    Lifecycle position - WHY Open / Investigation / parent Complaint case
    In Progress is meaningful:
      Per AAP Section 0.5.5 the resolve gate's GlideRecord query
      executed inside the validate_resolved_transition subflow is:

          var gr = new GlideRecord('x_casemgmt_case_task');
          gr.addQuery('case', current.sys_id);
          gr.addQuery('status', '!=', 'Closed');
          gr.query();
          if (gr.next()) {
              // BLOCK: surface the verbatim error message
              //   "All tasks must be closed before resolving this case."
          } else {
              // ALLOW: zero non-Closed tasks - case may be Resolved
          }

      Case 08 is in In Progress status with type=Complaint. With this
      Open child task PLUS task 06's In Progress status, the query
      "case = case 08 AND status != Closed" returns TWO rows. The
      subflow blocks any attempt to transition case 08 to Resolved and
      surfaces the verbatim error "All tasks must be closed before
      resolving this case." THIS TASK + TASK 06 ARE THE CANONICAL
      RESOLVE-BLOCKER PAIR FOR THE COMPLAINT FLOW. Where tasks 01 + 02
      perform this role for case 03 on the General Inquiry flow, this
      task with task 06 performs the same role for case 08 on the
      Complaint flow.

      The Investigation task type captures the agent's evidence-
      gathering action prior to taking substantive case action. Per
      the AAP's Complaint case-handling pattern, an investigation prep
      task (such as preparing for a witness interview) is a typical
      early step in the agent's workflow - the agent organizes
      questions, reviews prior evidence, and prepares any necessary
      documentation BEFORE conducting the interview itself. The
      "Witness interview prep" subject makes this lifecycle phase
      explicit. Note: per AAP Section 0.5.7's role_label examples, the
      term "Witness" is a generic party role label (alongside
      "Requester" and "Respondent"), NOT a real person's name; this
      task's subject uses the role label generically and contains
      zero PII.

      The +3 days due_date is appropriate for a near-term prep task -
      the agent has 3 calendar days to complete the prep before the
      scheduled interview. This contrasts with task 06's +7 days
      due_date (the broader investigation milestone is further out),
      reinforcing that prep tasks are typically scheduled more
      proximally than the activities they support. The relative date
      pattern uses positive offsets (in 3 days) for active/upcoming
      tasks, consistent with Open status semantics (a task that has
      not yet been started but has a target completion date).

